Paschasius Berselius (†May fin. 1535), was born at Bierset, 5 miles West of Liege. He is said to have made his profession at the Benedictine Abbey of St. Laurence, Liege, 3 July 1502 ; but as he is styled iuuenis in 1519 (Ep. 926. 18). the date seems doubt-ful. For some years he was resident in Liege, and enjoyed the confidence of Bp.
